<br>
For example, in the course of this discussion, I'm sure we will have a situation whereby some people will agree that FG's should be scheduled 24/7. Others will say 2 days a week. Others still will say not at all.<br>
<br>
Well, it is hardly fair if the vote turns out: <br>
<br>
Option 1. Reserve FG's 24/7<br>
Option 2. Reserve FG's 2 days a week<br>
Option 3. Reserve FG's not at all.<br>
<br>
In essence, the vote will be breaking up those who favor reserving FG's and leaving the &quot;FCFS&quot; crowd once again as a united voting front.<br>
<br>
Additionally, I think it's important that we talk about a mechanism whereby we find that it's helpful/necessary to add new mobs to the reservable list.<br>
<br>
For example, suppose everyone resolved that for now, leaving Phinny and FG's as reservable, due to their &quot;planes newbie/training&quot; nature.  However, later on, we find that CoM is starting to get raided a LOT and some people are stepping on toes. Or, even more importantly, the very highest levels are starting to get crowded again. (It will happen. It has happened before and the area is finite.)<br>
<br>
When demand exceeds supply, conflicts will happen. It happened on the planes, and we fixed that...when do we decide it happens elsewhere.. (PoG very soon, for example.)<br>
<br>
Sylvaen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/ugoatfrenesi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goat Frenesi</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Frenzied One</span><br>  Posts: 286<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/20/01 10:49:43 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/goatsghetto/uglymug.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Evaulation of &quot;Reservable&quot; Zones</span><hr size=1> Right now, the vote will be a simply yes/no if you want them reservable at this point.  The idea of hybrid reservation does sound interesting, but I haven't seen enough dissection of it to truely make it an option. <p><table border="0" width="350" cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td width="100%"><center><font face="Arial" size="1"><a href="http://sr.amiga.tm/cgi-bin/members.cgi?show=Kambing">Kambing Ebonhoof</a> the Disciple</font></center></td></tr><tr><td width="100%"><center><font face="Arial" size="1">PR Officer of <a href="http://sr.amiga.tm">Silent Redemption</a> - <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net">Brell Serilis</a></font></center></td></tr><tr><td width="100%"><center><font face="Arial" size="1">A (skeletal) Goat's Life, <a href="http://www.geocities.com/goatsghetto/goatslife">check it</a></font></center></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/umaryinnmb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maryinn MB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/20/01 11:25:00 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.merryband.com/images/maryinn/maryinn.jpg width=150 height=177></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Evaulation of &quot;Reservable&quot; Zones</span><hr size=1> I think that a partial reservation is going to be the best way to deal with the contested zones listed above.  If there are enough people who want to see Phinny or CoM or Chardok reserved, but not an overwhelming majority perhaps we could designate 2 days a week as &quot;reservation days&quot;.<br>
<br>
The most conveniant way to do this would be to have the same 2 (or however many) days be reservation days for all the disputed zones.  For instance have Sunday and Monday allow reservable raids for all the zones which people vote they need reservation times and the rest of the week is First Come First Served.  This way it's easy to remember when they need to check the board and when they don't.<br>
<br>
My personal opinion is that none of these zones should be reserved, there just aren't enough crowding issues in any of these places to warrant it.  However, if the votes are split fairly evenly this might be an acceptable compromise.  Just an idea. <p>-<a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=998">Maryinn</a> 
