<br>
/sigh<br>
<br>
Oh well, maybe I'll respond here to the people from the Phinny thread.<br>
<br>
First, let me start with the arguments I've seen in several weeks of talking about this.<br>
<br>
Why NOT to reserve something. Wait a sec.. let's make it interesting.. 10 (if I can find them) most popular reasons why NOT to reserve something.<br>
<br>
10. Removes the spontaneity of the game.<br>
<br>
9.  Because people can now do those mobs and don't require organization.<br>
<br>
8. Get some friends, you losers. &quot;I can find enough people to raid X mob w/out even asking anyone from my guild.&quot;<br>
<br>
7. Other servers don't reserve mobs, and they're just fine.<br>
<br>
6. &quot;The game is working as intended.&quot; (IE, w/out reservations.)<br>
<br>
5. If the mob is taken, just go find another one.<br>
<br>
4. &quot;I don't want to have to check my daytimer, everytime I want to go kill a mob.&quot;<br>
<br>
3. &quot;Just because.&quot;<br>
<br>
2. Most have epics involved which makes it even SLOWER to get your epics.<br>
<br>
And the #1 reason why NOT to make mobs reservable IS!<br>
<br>
1. If we reserve one thing, it's never going to stop and everything will become reservable!<br>
<br>
Now for the annoying part.. rebutting the damn things. I've only done it like 3 times in other threads.<br>
<br>
10. &quot;Waaa!&quot; Okay.. minus the sarcasm, the game is extremely spontaneous as it is. You rarely know exactly what you're going to do when you log on.  Even the most elite guilds have to plan a large raid. Why is it okay for them to plan a raid on a plane, but it's not okay for a smaller guild to raid Phinny?<br>
<br>
Cuz it's reserved? Oh yeah, that's right. But that's what we're trying to do, reserve a few more mobs for the same reasons the other stuff was reserved.<br>
<br>
9. Right. And as it happens, what people are basically saying is that back when they needed help and organization, it was okay for them, but NOW, that they don't need it, well, let's do away with it then. Why is that? Is that not an extremely selfish and self-centered attitude? Is that what Brell is about?<br>
<br>
8. See 9.<br>
<br>
7. No, they're not fine. Do we want to become what others are? If not, I highly suggest those people who can MOST benefit from FCFS now, watch your backs. People won't be level 35 forever. And they WILL remember who set the motions for FCFS.<br>
<br>
6. Sha.  Verant has many reasons for stating that. For one thing, they don't WANT to police every server. That costs MONEY. They do what they can with as little effort as possible.. thus, things like the PNP come into play. They encourage people to police themselves. Sometimes it works (Brell) sometimes it doesn't. (Veeshan, and others.) I don't think anyone on Brell is a big fan of &quot;uber&quot; guilds, and I don't think we have ANY in fact. (By definition, I would think an Uber guild is not a euphemism for &quot;big guild&quot; or even &quot;powerful guild&quot; but rather &quot;own the server&quot; guild... But that's another topic altogether.) Since we DO police ourselves, voting on things like this is what makes Verant's &quot;Working as intended&quot; statement true. As opposed to some casual aside of &quot;Let's do whatever the hell we want, cuz Verant says it's okay.&quot;<br>
<br>
5. Could be a good point. Except, there are few mobs with that same &quot;je no se quois&quot;. In other words, at level 45, phinny and the FG's have very few comparisons. You can't just take 18 level 45's to the Lord room in Guk. You can't take them to SolB, or even Karnor's.. (well, with the exception of the hand/warlord room, but that's hardly a raid.) They'd prolly get creamed anyway. Not to mention, the fact that FG's and Phinny are a TIMED spawn which means what they have is VALUABLE, giving a completely different aspect to a RAID than a simple dungeon crawl to Guk or Droga.<br>
<br>
4. For one thing, it's not every mob. We're talking adding a few mobs to the list. I also think that most people WILL be able to work out a compromise of some sort. Perhaps making weekends the only time for reserving mobs. (Hey, if you are so slick you can do any mob with six people, you don't NEED weekends to reserve the mobs.)  Additionally, RE: the &quot;checking the daytimer&quot; .. that HAS to be faster than sending your local druid over to the dungeon in question to see if the mob is taken. I don't care if it's as little as 15 mins to check a dungeon.. unless someone is IN that dungeon, checking a board is faster.<br>
<br>
3. Yes, I've heard that as a reason. Typically it's phrased as &quot;I vote no.&quot; with no reason or justification behind it. Talk about conservative minded. I mean, I'm a republican, but that's taking conservative thinking (backwards, closeminded, whatever label you want) to new heights. Open your ears and minds, people.<br>
<br>
2. Not really a valid  reason, since that point could be argued both ways. B/C it's involved with an epic, more fights will evolve over said mob, and as demand exceeds supply, conflicts will DEFINITELY happen. Just remember those cabbage patch dolls from the 80's. Man, you saw mothers fighting daughters, grammas leaping from wheelchairs. What a scene. <br>
<br>
No one is saying we can only kill a said mob, once a day. No reason we can't update the FG's so that we can kill them twice a day. Ditto on Phinny.. perhaps even three times. If the demand for reserved spots gets so high, then we know we took the right track. If not, at least we are doing the right thing for people who need reservations.<br>
<br>
1. I find this the most pathetic excuse of all.  I mean, c'mon. Talk about doomsday prophecies.  No one has of yet asked (at its worst) that all mobs become reservable, yet people are just automagically assuming that that is what's going to happen. No reason.. no logic. Just jumping to conclusions. So we never reserve another mob, because next thing you know, orc 1 in EC is going to be reserved... words fail me.<br>
<br>
Btw, I'm mostly for Phinny being reserved. I had to nod in favor of Adune's and Sindarre's reasoning (from the previous post started by Kruunch) in regards to the spawn times of Chardok, CoM, and the other reservable mobs. If it's only a few hours, then it really starts falling into the &quot;normal camp spot&quot; timeframe.  Eight hours, however, is one excessive camp!<br>
<br>
My fight has mostly been about Phinny. I'm even amenable to having it just two days a week, provided we leave the option open that if those slots get used a lot, we can expand it.. (to 3.. maybe to.. gasp.. 4?) eventually. <br>
<br>
Let's BE openminded. Let's BE Brell.<br>
<br>
Sylvaen, 54 chanter of Brell<br>
